Introduction

PRITTI-G (Korean: 프리티지), formerly known as PRITTI (프리티) was a girl group that started under IN Entertainment, who debuted in 2015, however, in December 2020, it was announced that the group would be under ENTERROBANG and its name would be changed to PRITTI-G. During pre-debut, PRITTI-G was composed of 6 members (Yeryang, Sarang, Sojeong, Chaeryun, Yoonji and Jiyoung), during debut contained only 5 (Yeryang, Sarang, Sojeong, Yoonji and Jiyoung) and, after the Yoonji left, the group stayed with only 4 members, which is the current lineup. They disbanded without any official announcements in mid 2023.
